# Se cumplen los supuestos de los residuos homecedasticidad. Sin embargo, no se cumple el supuesto de normalidad, ni linealidad de los residuos por lo que el modelo puede que no sea el mejor.

lm(formula = velmax ~ svl_cm * peso_g * Reservas_energeticas, 
    data = costos)

We fitted a linear model (estimated using OLS) to predict velmax with svl_cm, peso_g and Reservas_energeticas (formula:
velmax ~ svl_cm * peso_g * Reservas_energeticas). The model explains a statistically not significant and moderate proportion
of variance (R2 = 0.21, F(7, 40) = 1.49, p = 0.200, adj. R2 = 0.07). The model's intercept, corresponding to svl_cm = 0,
peso_g = 0 and Reservas_energeticas = 0, is at 0.22 (95% CI [-4.61, 5.05], t(40) = 0.09, p = 0.927). Within this model:

  - The effect of svl cm is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 0.05, 95% CI [-0.20, 0.31], t(40) = 0.42, p =
0.676; Std. beta = 0.09, 95% CI [-0.45, 0.63])
  - The effect of peso g is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 1.27, 95% CI [-5.49, 8.02], t(40) = 0.38, p =
0.707; Std. beta = 0.31, 95% CI [-0.15, 0.77])
  - The effect of Reservas energeticas is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 3.50, 95% CI [-7.25, 14.25],
t(40) = 0.66, p = 0.514; Std. beta = -0.02, 95% CI [-0.43, 0.38])
  - The effect of svl cm √ó peso g is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.07, 95% CI [-0.41, 0.28], t(40) =
-0.39, p = 0.701; Std. beta = 0.16, 95% CI [-0.25, 0.57])
  - The effect of svl cm √ó Reservas energeticas is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.19, 95% CI [-0.75,
0.37], t(40) = -0.69, p = 0.494; Std. beta = -0.08, 95% CI [-0.71, 0.54])
  - The effect of peso g √ó Reservas energeticas is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -5.21, 95% CI [-20.85,
10.42], t(40) = -0.67, p = 0.504; Std. beta = 0.23, 95% CI [-0.44, 0.90])
  - The effect of (svl cm √ó peso g) √ó Reservas energeticas is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 0.29, 95% CI
[-0.51, 1.08], t(40) = 0.72, p = 0.473; Std. beta = 0.17, 95% CI [-0.30, 0.64])

Standardized parameters were obtained by fitting the model on a standardized version of the dataset. 95% Confidence
Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald t-distribution approximation.
